# UI Layout Patterns

Use flex-wrap responsive layouts for forms and detail pages.

## Section Cards

```tsx
// Consistent section styling
const sectionClass = "rounded-lg border bg-card overflow-hidden";
const sectionHeaderClass = "bg-muted/70 px-3 py-2 border-b";
const sectionTitleClass = "text-sm font-semibold text-foreground";
const sectionContentClass = "p-3";

// Card with responsive sizing
<section className={`${sectionClass} w-full sm:w-auto sm:min-w-[280px] sm:flex-1`}>
  <div className={sectionHeaderClass}>
    <h3 className={sectionTitleClass}>Section Title</h3>
  </div>
  <div className={sectionContentClass}>...</div>
</section>
```

## Layout Containers

```tsx
// Section grid - wraps dynamically
<div className="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
  {/* Section cards here */}
</div>

// Field grid within sections
<div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
  {/* Field wrappers here */}
</div>
```

## Form Field Sizing (mobile-first)

Below `sm`, each field is full width so they don't squash on mobile. From `sm` up, fields wrap with min-widths and take full width when alone on a line.

```tsx
const fieldClass = "space-y-1 w-full min-w-0 sm:min-w-[100px] sm:flex-1";           // Standard
const dateFieldClass = "space-y-1 w-full min-w-0 sm:min-w-[160px] sm:flex-1";        // Date pickers
const wideFieldClass = "space-y-1 w-full min-w-0 sm:min-w-[140px] sm:flex-1";       // Wider fields
const narrowFieldClass = "space-y-1 w-full min-w-0 sm:min-w-[70px] sm:flex-1 sm:max-w-[100px]"; // Constrained (max-w from sm only)
```

## Action button groups

For groups of action buttons (e.g. Quick Actions), use full width on mobile and auto width from `sm` so they align and flow nicely:

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
  <div className="w-full min-w-0 sm:w-auto">
    <Link to="..." className="block">
      <Button variant="outline" className="w-full sm:w-auto">Label</Button>
    </Link>
  </div>
  {/* more actions */}
</div>
```

## Detail Pages

Dashboard style: header card (photo + name + actions) above info cards grid.

```tsx
// Info row for label/value pairs
function InfoRow({ label, value }: { label: string; value: React.ReactNode }) {
  if (!value) return null;
  return (
    <div className="flex gap-2">
      <span className="text-muted-foreground shrink-0">{label}:</span>
      <span>{value}</span>
    </div>
  );
}
```
